# Feature-Sliced Design (FSD) Architecture Rules

## Layer Structure
The project follows FSD architecture with these layers (from top to bottom):
- `app/` - Initialization, configuration, providers
- `pages/` - Page components (composition of widgets and features)
- `widgets/` - Complex composite components
- `features/` - Business functionality
- `entities/` - Business entities with API
- `shared/` - Reusable components, utilities, API

## Import Rules (CRITICAL)
**Imports can only go DOWN the layers, never up:**
- `app` → can import from all layers
- `pages` → can import from `widgets`, `features`, `entities`, `shared`
- `widgets` → can import from `features`, `entities`, `shared`
- `features` → can import from `entities`, `shared`
- `entities` → can import from `shared` only
- `shared` → cannot import from any other layer

**NEVER import from:**
- Higher layers (e.g., `entities` cannot import from `features`)
- Same layer (e.g., `features/auth` cannot import from `features/user`)
- Sibling slices (e.g., `entities/user` cannot import from `entities/request`)

## Path Aliases
Always use path aliases instead of relative imports:
- `@app/*` for app layer
- `@pages/*` for pages layer
- `@widgets/*` for widgets layer
- `@features/*` for features layer
- `@entities/*` for entities layer
- `@shared/*` for shared layer
- `@locales/*` for locales

Example: `import { Button } from '@shared/ui/button'` not `import { Button } from '../../../shared/ui/button'`

## Entity Structure
Each entity should follow this structure:
```
entities/entity-name/
├── api/           # API calls, services
├── hooks/         # React hooks (useEntity, useEntities)
├── model/         # Types, schemas, constants
├── schemas/       # Zod validation schemas
├── services/      # Business logic services
├── types/         # TypeScript types
└── index.ts       # Public API exports
```

## Feature Structure
Each feature should follow this structure:
```
features/feature-name/
├── ui/            # UI components
├── hooks/         # Feature-specific hooks
├── model/         # Feature state, types
└── index.ts       # Public API exports
```

## Widget Structure
Each widget should follow this structure:
```
widgets/widget-name/
├── WidgetName.tsx # Main component
└── index.ts       # Public API exports
```

## Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (`UserCard.tsx`, `CreateRequestButton.tsx`)
- **Hooks**: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useRequests.ts`, `useAuth.tsx`)
- **Services**: camelCase (`requestService.ts`, `authService.ts`)
- **Types**: PascalCase (`Request.ts`, `User.ts`)
- **Schemas**: camelCase with `Schema` suffix (`requestSchema.ts`, `authSchema.ts`)
- **Constants**: camelCase (`const.ts`)

## Public API
- Always export public API through `index.ts` files
- Never import from internal files (e.g., `./model/types.ts`), always use `index.ts`
- Keep internal implementation details private

## Shared Layer
- `shared/ui/` - Reusable UI components (shadcn/ui components)
- `shared/api/` - API configuration, axios instance, mock data
- `shared/utils/` - Utility functions
- `shared/config/` - Configuration files
